Fans may bring food into the stadium on game days in clear plastic bags only, but no beverages will be allowed per NFL policy. Flash photography, video cameras and support tools (such as tripods, large lens, etc.) are not allowed. Smoking and tobacco use are prohibited in all areas of Lumen Field and Event Center. All fans must abide by the Fan Code of Conduct. For full rules and policies please visit www.seahawks.com.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: ADDRESS: 754 Silica Road NW George, Washington 98848 Phone (509) 785-6262 Email: gorgeinfo@livenation.com
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: For the safety of our employees and guests, the box office will be closed until further notice. Please keep checking back here for updates as to when we re-open. We appreciate your understanding.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: U.S. Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets held at will call can be picked up on the day of the performance during the Box Office hours of operation. (Subject to change). The customer must present a valid form of identification, the actual credit card used, and the confirmation number to pick up their tickets.

venues.parkingDetail: Lot opening times vary by show, but usually open 4 hours before posted event start time. PLEASE CALL THE VENUE AT 509-785-6262 FOR FURTHER INFORMATION The Gorge Amphitheatre has two parking options; Regular or STAR Parking. Designated parking area for physically challenged patrons is available at the front gate. Please follow the signs or parking staff direction upon entering the main lot. The parking lot gate, normally opens at 12:00pm, Although times may vary depending on the event. Sorry, no overnight parking. (See “Gorge Camping”) STAR PARKING: Upgrade to STAR Parking for convenient parking. Benefit from the easy access and exit to and from this reserved parking lot. You will be guaranteed a spot within easy reach of the main gates.. For overnight stays please see the camping section. Please note: By order of the Grant County Sheriff's Department, there is no parking or camping on county roads or private property leading to or adjacent to the venue. The county ordinances strictly prohibit the consumption of alcoholic beverages in the parking lot, and these laws will be strictly enforced.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible Seating, please inform your Ticketmaster representative (if you are calling) or requesting on-line, if you need reserved seating or general admission seating. With each accessible seat purchased, up to 3 companion tickets may be purchased. Anyone who is disabled and not in a wheelchair can request to use a folding chair for use in this space. Please contact a staff member for assistance. Please note there is NOT an accessible seating purchase option in general admission. Should you need accessible assistance in the general admission section, please visit a Guest Services kiosk after entering the venue for relocation to the accessible section of the lawn. For those needing assistance, a special services vehicle can transport physically challenged patrons near to their seating section, for more information: https://www.livenation.com/venues/14067/gorge-amphitheatre Only trained service animals are allowed into the Amphitheatre

generalInfo.generalRule: For the safety of all Gorge patrons, please follow these simple rules: * No alcoholic beverages can be brought into the venue. There are alcohol beverage stands and lounges where you may purchase throughout the venue. Please bring a valid WA State approved ID. Acceptable forms of ID: A Driver License, ID Card, or Instruction Permit issued by any U.S. State or Canadian Province. A Washington Temporary Driver License (paper license). A U.S. Military ID. An Official Passport. A Merchant Marine ID. A Washington State Tribal Enrollment Card. ALL RULES SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE. Beer and wine can be purchased and can be taken to your seat in General Admission or Reserved areas. • No lounge and elevated chairs. Beach style are OK and rental chairs are available. • No laser pointers • Empty plastic drinking water containers will be allowed in. One factory sealed water bottles of 20 oz. size will be allowed in. Sorry, no factory sealed soda bottles please. • Food in clear plastic gallon sized bag (one per patron) will also be allowed in. No large, hard-shelled coolers or ice chests. • School-size or small backpacks are normally allowed in, but may be subject to change at the artists request. All bags are subject to visual search. NO Large Backpacks. • Emergency medical personnel and ambulance transport is on site. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Subject to change at the artists request.
generalInfo.childRule: Children under the age of 2 are free in General Admission Lawn seating. Every one including Children will require a reserved ticket to access the reserved seating area. All ages are allowed inside the amphitheatre.

venues.parkingDetail: Lumen Field manages three parking lots: the North Lot, Lumen Field Event Center Garage, and Union Station Garage. Gameday parking costs may vary. For further information please call the Seahawks ticket office at 1-888-NFL-HAWK (1-888-635-4295) or visit www.ipmseattle.com
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: There are disabled seats (wheelchair convertible) dispersed through all areas and price levels of Lumen Field. Disabled seating and access for all is fully compliant with the Americans with Disabilities Act, (ADA).

generalInfo.generalRule: Due to NFL policy, no soft-sided containers, coolers, or large bags (bigger than 12" X 12" X 12") are permitted into Lumen Field for any event. Guests may bring in items in small, clear plastic bags. Event security is required to open all bags at the gates for a visual inspection before allowing guests' entry. Fans may bring food into the stadium on game days in clear plastic bags only, but no beverages will be allowed per NFL policy. Flash photography, video cameras and support tools (such as tripods, large lens, etc.) are not allowed. Smoking and tobacco use are prohibited in all areas of Lumen Field and Event Center. All fans must abide by the Fan Code of Conduct. For full rules and policies please visit www.seahawks.com.
generalInfo.childRule: Children under the age of 3 are free but must sit on adult's lap.

venues.name: Climate Pledge Arena

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Box Office is open 3 hours prior to the start of an event, located at the southwest corner of the Climate Pledge Arena Grounds at 1st & Thomas. It is open 2 hours prior to an event on Day Of Show for will call and sales for that day's performance only. We are a paperless venue and tickets will be sent via text.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Apple Pay, Visa, AMX, MC, and Discover. We do not accept cash or checks.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: WILL CALL LOCATION: SW Corner of Climate Pledge Arena on 1st & Thomas. WILL CALL OPENS: 2 hours prior to event time. DOORS OPEN: 1 hour prior to event time (Varies by Event).

venues.parkingDetail: Off-site pay lots and street parking (early arrival is recommended). On-site parking garages include Arena garage, 1st Ave garage, & 5th Ave garage. https://climatepledgearena.com/transportation/
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Parking - The 1st Ave N Garage is located 1 block south of Climate Pledge Arena. It is fully accessible with easy access to Climate Pledge Arena. Street parking & pay lots are also available but not as conveniently located. Drop Off - All Main Entrance doors to Climate Pledge Arena are accessible. The West entrance is the most convenient for drop off. 1st Ave N directly runs in front of the facility. Drop off location for the East entry is about 1/2 block away from Climate Pledge Arena at 2nd and Thomas. Entry - For most events, the West, South and East doors are open for entry.

generalInfo.childRule: Unless Otherwise noted, Children Under 3yrs are Free on Lap. All Ages allowed unless otherwise noted. For customer convenience, baby-changing stations are located in all restrooms at Climate Pledge Arena.

ada.adaCustomCopy: Accessible seating is available for guests with mobility disabilities and guests who require the accessible features provided in our accessible seating locations. When purchasing an accessible seat, up to 3 companion tickets may be purchased. Guest Services provides additional accommodations for guests as requested;  a full list of accommodations can be found at https://climatepledgearena.com/ticketing-guest-info . If you require interpretive services, please contact info@climatepledgearena.com or 206-460-7825 at least 7 days in advance of your event to reserve.

venues.name: Gorge Amphitheatre

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: ADDRESS: 754 Silica Road NW George, Washington 98848 Phone (509) 785-6262 Email: gorgeinfo@livenation.com
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: For the safety of our employees and guests, the box office will be closed until further notice. Please keep checking back here for updates as to when we re-open. We appreciate your understanding.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: U.S. Cash, MasterCard, Visa, American Express and Discover.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets held at will call can be picked up on the day of the performance during the Box Office hours of operation. (Subject to change). The customer must present a valid form of identification, the actual credit card used, and the confirmation number to pick up their tickets.

venues.parkingDetail: Lot opening times vary by show, but usually open 4 hours before posted event start time. PLEASE CALL THE VENUE AT 509-785-6262 FOR FURTHER INFORMATION The Gorge Amphitheatre has two parking options; Regular or STAR Parking. Designated parking area for physically challenged patrons is available at the front gate. Please follow the signs or parking staff direction upon entering the main lot. The parking lot gate, normally opens at 12:00pm, Although times may vary depending on the event. Sorry, no overnight parking. (See “Gorge Camping”) STAR PARKING: Upgrade to STAR Parking for convenient parking. Benefit from the easy access and exit to and from this reserved parking lot. You will be guaranteed a spot within easy reach of the main gates.. For overnight stays please see the camping section. Please note: By order of the Grant County Sheriff's Department, there is no parking or camping on county roads or private property leading to or adjacent to the venue. The county ordinances strictly prohibit the consumption of alcoholic beverages in the parking lot, and these laws will be strictly enforced.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible Seating, please inform your Ticketmaster representative (if you are calling) or requesting on-line, if you need reserved seating or general admission seating. With each accessible seat purchased, up to 3 companion tickets may be purchased. Anyone who is disabled and not in a wheelchair can request to use a folding chair for use in this space. Please contact a staff member for assistance. Please note there is NOT an accessible seating purchase option in general admission. Should you need accessible assistance in the general admission section, please visit a Guest Services kiosk after entering the venue for relocation to the accessible section of the lawn. For those needing assistance, a special services vehicle can transport physically challenged patrons near to their seating section, for more information: https://www.livenation.com/venues/14067/gorge-amphitheatre Only trained service animals are allowed into the Amphitheatre

generalInfo.generalRule: For the safety of all Gorge patrons, please follow these simple rules: * No alcoholic beverages can be brought into the venue. There are alcohol beverage stands and lounges where you may purchase throughout the venue. Please bring a valid WA State approved ID. Acceptable forms of ID: A Driver License, ID Card, or Instruction Permit issued by any U.S. State or Canadian Province. A Washington Temporary Driver License (paper license). A U.S. Military ID. An Official Passport. A Merchant Marine ID. A Washington State Tribal Enrollment Card. ALL RULES SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE. Beer and wine can be purchased and can be taken to your seat in General Admission or Reserved areas. • No lounge and elevated chairs. Beach style are OK and rental chairs are available. • No laser pointers • Empty plastic drinking water containers will be allowed in. One factory sealed water bottles of 20 oz. size will be allowed in. Sorry, no factory sealed soda bottles please. • Food in clear plastic gallon sized bag (one per patron) will also be allowed in. No large, hard-shelled coolers or ice chests. • School-size or small backpacks are normally allowed in, but may be subject to change at the artists request. All bags are subject to visual search. NO Large Backpacks. • Emergency medical personnel and ambulance transport is on site. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. Flash photography, video and removable lens cameras are not permitted without venue approval. Subject to change at the artists request.
generalInfo.childRule: Children under the age of 2 are free in General Admission Lawn seating. Every one including Children will require a reserved ticket to access the reserved seating area. All ages are allowed inside the amphitheatre.
